New Records: Travis Head scored the highest score by an Australian in an ODI in England with 154 not out
Key Match Events: Travis Head's unbeaten century helped Australia win the match by 7 wickets
Marnus Labuschagne made 77 not out and shared an unbroken match-winning partnership of 148 with Head
Adam Zampa took 3 wickets and Mitch Marsh relied on his part-time spinners to bowl out England for 315
Post-Match Reflections: Travis Head expressed that he has worked hard over the years and plays the game more relaxed now
Mitch Marsh was happy with the win, especially after England's start and the team's ability to pull it back
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ben Dwarshuis picked up an apparent shoulder injury and could only bowl four overs
England batted first after winning the toss and had a total of 315 off 49.4 overs
Jofra Archer had a terrific duel with Head, but Head later pulled him for six
Others: Harry Brook captained England in the absence of Jos Buttler
The second match of the series will be at Leeds on Saturday night
